name: Kashi Dairy veg restaurant

reviews.review_text:
Location is good - at a walkable distance both from Vasco Bus Stand and Vasco Railway Station.
The food is strictly veg and tastes excellent. Comparing the quantity and quality with other available options nearby, this restaurant is far better than anyone.
Behaviour of the staffs are excellent and response is also professional. The pricing of food is also very much affordable.
The only factor I've observed is it's seating capacity is not sufficient according to demand and number of customers incoming. Thus, always a waiting crowd may be seen during the peak hours.
Apart from this, like more other restaurants nearby, this place doesn't have any designated parking place available. The vehicles are to be parked on street on owner's own risk.
But, if you crave for some veg delicacies under pocket friendly budget, I would definitely recommend this place to visit once.

So a friend of mine randomly remembered this place where he had eaten this AMAZING paratha in 2008. Didn't remember anything but the taste of the paratha from back then. We googled the best paratha in Vasco, and this was one of the first places. We saw the photos and narrowed them down because this looked the best.

When my friend had the first bite, he knew this was the place we were looking for! Such is the taste of this place that everyone remembered it after 15-odd years!

The place is generally open very late, till 11 o'clock. There are two sittings, one non-ac on the ground floor and AC on the first floor.
They have takeaways as well, which probably comprise most of their orders. This can mean the service is slow, but that's not the case here. The staff is active, and the small kitchen on the first floor makes getting smaller things out quickly possible. But but, we've seen the waiter get lost and forget which table ordered the fried rice. So that was a meh.

We ordered the classic Aloo Paratha, which they serve hot with curd. We also ordered Matar Paneer because it was too late to eat curd. The paratha was stuffed and was more than enough for one person's meal. The matar paneer tasted really good as well.
Not sure if the AC/non-AC sitting has different prices, but the price was really affordable for the taste and the service in the AC section as well.

Overall, it was a great experience, mainly because of the story my friend had with the place. But kudos to the restaurant for not disappointing!
Would definitely recommend it for lunch/dinner if you like parathas.

Good food, chole bhature, samosa is the best small in size though as compare to price,
Chole bhature is an excellent choice and so does the pav bhaji
I will never prefer to order aloo Paratha here. Was not as per my expectations.
Lassi is must try..
Massala Dosa is ok, but not as per mark..

description:
### Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant: A Culinary Haven in Vasco da Gama

Located conveniently close to both the Vasco Bus Stand and Railway Station, Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant boasts a commendable rating of 3.8 based on 926 reviews. Renowned for its delicious vegetarian offerings, the eatery's specialties include **Aloo Paratha** and **Lassi**, which consistently receive high praise from patrons. With tags like "samosa" and "hotel" also making the list, it’s clear that this restaurant has carved out a reputation among locals and visitors alike.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon stepping into Kashi Dairy, diners are greeted by a lively atmosphere that reflects the essence of casual dining. The restaurant features two seating options: an air-conditioned space on the first floor and a non-AC area on the ground floor. Reviewers have noted that while the small establishment often sees a waiting crowd during peak hours, the ambiance remains welcoming and vibrant. The photos reveal a clean and practical décor, with well-utilized space, though some guests have commented on the need for more seating to accommodate the growing demand.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Kashi Dairy is extensive for a vegetarian restaurant, though certain dishes are standout favorites. The **Aloo Paratha** is a hallmark item—served hot with curd—and is deemed substantial enough for a satisfying meal. Reviewers have fondly reminisced about their experiences with this dish, showcasing its lasting impression. Other notable mentions include **Chole Bhature**, which one reviewer described as "excellent," and **Lassi**, a must-try for those seeking a refreshing beverage to accompany their meal. While some dishes, like the **Masala Dosa**, received mixed reviews, the overall culinary quality and affordability have garnered acclaim, making it a budget-friendly option for vibrant vegetarian cuisine.

### Customer Experience & Service

Guests frequently commend the staff’s professionalism and prompt service, attributing a positive dining experience to their attentiveness even during busy times. The restaurant also offers takeaways, contributing to its popularity, though some diners have observed minor lapses in order management during peak hours. The affordable pricing and the atmosphere make it a go-to spot for both casual lunches and hearty dinners. However, it is advisable to arrive early during peak dining hours due to the limited seating.

### Popularity & Reviews

Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant certainly holds its own in the competitive dining landscape of Vasco da Gama. The eatery has garnered a loyal following, with many customers frequently returning for the comfort food that reminds them of past delightful experiences—one reviewer even noted a fan returning after 15 years just for the **Aloo Paratha**! The restaurant enjoys notable recognition on social media, where patrons share photographs and rave about their favorite dishes, creating a buzz that has strengthened its local presence.

### Utilizing Visual Content

Images shared by diners beautifully convey the culinary appeal of Kashi Dairy. A glimpse into the dishes reveals generously stuffed **Aloo Parathas**, inviting **Lassi**, and appealing **Chole Bhature** mounds, each presented as a delightful feast. The restaurant's interior, as depicted through customers' photos, showcases a simple yet engaging atmosphere, emphasizing the focus on food and customer experience rather than elaborate décor.

In summary, Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant exceeds expectations with its affordable vegetarian fare and commendable service, making it a beloved destination for locals and travelers alike. Whether you're craving a classic **Aloo Paratha** or simply wish to enjoy a delicious meal in a friendly environment, this establishment promises satisfaction at every turn.
